                {"$": "Moreover, there should be clear separation between the provision of basic pension and poverty alleviation programs. For poverty alleviation programs, the government should provide support to all individuals in need, not restricting to older persons. One such scheme in Thailand is the state welfare card, which allows people to register and define themselves as poor to receive support from the government in the form of cash cards to buy basic commodities (Kamnuansilpa, ). Another example is the financial support to families in need provided by the Ministry of Social Development and Human Security. The scheme provides financial support of 3,000 baht per time, no more than 3 times per family per year, to families facing adversity and in need of support (Ministry of Social Development and Human Security, )."}
